### SMTPUTF8 Syntax
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-mailmaint-smtputf8-syntax`
* **Presenter:** Arnt Gulbrandsen
* **Slides:** [SMTPUTF8 syntax](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mailmaint-smtputf8-syntax-00)
* **Overview:** Arnt Gulbrandsen proposed updating RFC 6532 to introduce stricter constraints on which Unicode code points can appear together in the local-part of an email address. This prevents rendering and security issues without altering the core ABNF structure.
* **Rules without ABNF:** John Klensin expressed general support for defining rules textually rather than in ABNF, but cautioned that the intersection of UAX 31 (Unicode Identifier and Pattern Syntax) and IDNA 2008 must be checked carefully. 
* **Message/Global Encoding Issue:** Victor Duchovni argued that RFC 6532 Section 3.7 (specifying `message/global`) was a design mistake that allows non-identity transfer encoding. Arnt Gulbrandsen and Alexey Melnikov agreed but recommended addressing the `message/global` issue in a separate follow-up document to avoid delaying the progress of the SMTPUTF8 syntax draft. Victor agreed to post suggestions on this topic to the mailing list.

