### IMAP Object ID Bis & Extension Suggestions
* **Drafts:** `draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-objectid-bis` and `draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-extensions-suggestions`
* **Presenters:** Ricardo Signes, Bron Gondwana, Michael Slusarz
* **Flag Handling in Object ID Bis:** Bron Gondwana discussed the challenge of ensuring flags are exposed identically across multiple copies of an email. Under JMAP philosophy, flags must be identical for all instances of the same email ID. Bron committed to updating the Cyrus IMAP server to enforce this identical flag behavior. Arnt Gulbrandsen agreed that this flag handling design is optimal.
* **Implementation Status:** Alexey Melnikov noted that the response format has changed, meaning client-side implementation is needed before the draft can progress. Arnt Gulbrandsen and Bron Gondwana committed to writing client-side implementations (including within a JMAP proxy).
* **IMAP Extension Suggestions:** Michael Slusarz reported that `draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-extensions-suggestions` remains parked until `draft-ietf-mailmaint-imap-objectid-bis` is finalized to ensure correct Object ID integration.

